name: market for strawberry seedling, for planting | strawberry seedling, for planting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/14997/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'strawberry seedling, for planting', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product 'strawberry seedling, for planting' represents 1 strawberry seedling. It is a perennial crop. This product is used for plant propagation. A seedling is a young plant raised from seed in a nursery.  The seedlings are produced in a greenhouse (heated or unheated). 

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'strawberry seedling, for planting',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of 'strawberry seedling, for planting',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.
